The Automobile Association believes the petrol price could decrease by 24 cents per litre. CAPE TOWN - There could be some good news for South Africans, with a drop in fuel prices expected next week.The Automobile Association (AA) believes the petrol price could decrease by 24 cents per litre.The AA s Layton Beard says: International petroleum prices continue to reach an ease during March on the back of an increase in global stocks. Over the same period, the rand performed strongly against the US dollar, obviously not with recent events. Beard says this comes despite an increase in both the fuel levy and contribution to the Road Accident Fund which kicks in this month.(Edited by Shimoney Regter)